  "body": "#### System information\r\nGeth version: 1.8.1-stable\r\nOS & Version: Linux CentOS Linux release 7.4.1708 (Core)\r\nGo Version: go1.10\r\nTestnet: Rinkeby\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\neth.getTransactionReceipt() returns null if the transaction is submitted but not mined.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nThrows \"Error: unknown transaction\". This confuses apps, hard to estimate the actual status of transactions. Please refer https://github.com/web3j/web3j/issues/318\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nSend a transaction and get transaction receipt immediately before it's mined.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n> eth.getTransactionReceipt(\"0x691441440f59e6756a5c8608d239a8728a5c12d09a8cdf6339478a5638be1e85\")\r\nError: unknown transaction\r\n    at web3.js:3143:20\r\n    at web3.js:6347:15\r\n    at web3.js:5081:36\r\n    at <anonymous>:1:1\r\n````\r\n",
